			<p><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> <date>May 17. 1852</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Would you be good enough to trans&#45;<lb/>late the enclosed into English and include it in<lb/> your next number of your periodical. Before you<lb/> left this place I thought you would pay me a<lb/> visit. It seems&#44; however&#44; that you did not<lb/> think of keeping your promise&#44; or that your de&#45;<lb/>parture was rushed. Would you please send<lb/> me a copy of the translation&#44; for I may want<lb/> to have it included in a local newspaper&#44; pro&#45;<lb/>vided it seems learned enough. Let me know<lb/> when your next number appears.</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">Respectfully&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">C. Nussbaum</persName>&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)">Dealer in books&#44; groceries<lb/> and citrons.</p>
			<p>I hope you won&#39;t forget to have my<lb/> name printed with the above description.</p>
          
        </body>
